@startuml er_memory_store
' Source:  docs/CT/DATA/ (no dedicated data contract — memory is in-process)
' Store:   Memory Store — ~/.nasim/memory/{scope}/{key}.json (JSON Lines)
' Legend:  * = mandatory;  <<PK>> = primary key;  <<FK>> = foreign key
' ============================================================
' Title:     nasim — Memory Store ERD
' Boundary:  NASIM Application — Memory Repository owns this store
' Purpose:   Enhanced memory schema with RAG support
' Milestone: v1.0
' Version:   2.0.0
' Source:    docs/audit/audit_2026-06-20_capability-and-architecture.md
' Review:    —
' Note:      RAG-enhanced memory with vector embeddings and
'            TF-IDF keyword index for hybrid retrieval.
'            Physical storage: ~/.nasim/memory/
' ============================================================

title nasim — Memory Store ERD

entity "memory_entry" as me {
    * id : TEXT (UUID) <<PK>>
    --
    * scope : TEXT {global|project|session}
    * key : TEXT
    * content : TEXT
    embedding : BLOB
    metadata : TEXT (JSON)
    * created_at : TEXT (ISO 8601)
    * updated_at : TEXT (ISO 8601)
}

entity "episodic_entry" as ee {
    * id : TEXT (UUID) <<PK>>
    * session_id : TEXT <<FK>>
    --
    * summary : TEXT
    embedding : BLOB
    * turn_range_start : INTEGER
    * turn_range_end : INTEGER
    * created_at : TEXT (ISO 8601)
}

entity "semantic_entry" as se {
    * id : TEXT (UUID) <<PK>>
    * fact : TEXT
    embedding : BLOB
    * source_session : TEXT <<FK>>
    * confidence : REAL
    tags : TEXT (JSON)
    * created_at : TEXT (ISO 8601)
}

entity "memory_index" as mi {
    * entry_id : TEXT <<FK>>
    * token : TEXT
    --
    tfidf_weight : REAL
}

entity "memory_fts" as mfts {
    * memory_entry_id : TEXT <<FK>>
    --
    * content : TEXT (FTS5 indexed)
    * key : TEXT (FTS5 indexed)
    scope : TEXT (FTS5 indexed)
}

me ||--o{ mfts : "content indexed by"
me ||--o{ mi : "token indexed by"
ee }o--|| me : "belongs to"
se }o--|| me : "references"

note bottom of me
  Physical storage: ~/.nasim/memory/
  Core memory entries with optional vector embeddings.
  Scope determines visibility and persistence level.
  TF-IDF keyword index enables hybrid retrieval
  (semantic similarity + keyword matching).
  FTS5 virtual table (memory_fts) provides SQLite
  full-text search with BM25 ranking for keyword queries.

  Notation:
    * prefix = Mandatory (NOT NULL)
    <<PK>> = Primary key
    <<FK>> = Foreign key
    {A|B|C} = Enum constraint
    TEXT (JSON) = JSON blob stored as TEXT
    BLOB = Binary vector embedding data
    REAL = Floating point value
    FTS5 = SQLite full-text search virtual table
end note

note bottom of ee
  Episodic memory: summaries of conversation turns.
  Embedding enables semantic search over past sessions.
  Turn range enables partial session replay.
end note

note bottom of se
  Semantic memory: extracted facts with confidence scores.
  Source session provides provenance.
  Tags enable faceted filtering.
end note

note right of mi
  Inverted index for keyword search.
  Each entry is decomposed into tokens
  with TF-IDF weights for ranking.
end note

@enduml
